# Development Environment Setup

This guide sets up a full development environment for **<<PROJECT_NAME>>**. For a plain install,
see the [README](README.md#installation).

## Prerequisites

| Tool | Version | Why |
|------|---------|-----|
| Python | >= <<PYTHON_VERSION>> | Runtime |
| [Poetry](https://python-poetry.org) | 1.7+ | Dependency & environment management |
| `make` | any | Task runner / dev UX |
| Node.js | 18+ | Building the Antora docs site (optional) |
| Docker + Compose | recent | Running the local stack (optional) |

## 1. Clone and install

```bash
git clone https://github.com/<<GITHUB_ORG>>/<<PROJECT_SLUG>>.git
cd <<PROJECT_SLUG>>
make install        # poetry install with dev, test, and lint groups
```

`make install` does **not** run `poetry lock`. Lock dependencies explicitly with `make lock` when
you change them.

## 2. Enable pre-commit hooks

The repo ships a pre-commit config (Ruff format + lint) so style issues are caught before they
reach CI:

```bash
poetry run pre-commit install
poetry run pre-commit run --all-files   # optional: check the whole tree once
```

## 3. Verify the environment

```bash
make check-all      # lint, type-check, architecture, tests
```

A green run means your environment matches CI.

## 4. (Optional) Run the local stack with Docker

If the project ships infra under `infra/`:

```bash
cp infra/.env.example infra/.env        # then fill in any required values
make up                                 # start the stack
make logs                               # follow logs
make down                               # stop the stack
```

> The Docker ignore file lives at `infra/docker/Dockerfile.dockerignore` (Docker auto-discovers
> `<dockerfile>.dockerignore`), not at the repository root.

## 5. (Optional) Build the docs locally

```bash
make install-antora # first time only
make preview-docs   # serve at http://localhost:8080
```

## Troubleshooting

- **Wrong Python interpreter** — always invoke tools through Poetry (`poetry run …`) or `make`,
  never a global `python`/`pytest`.
- **`CLAUDE.md` looks like a duplicate** — it is a symlink to `AGENTS.md`. Leave it alone.
